<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys..62046.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Morphological features of Trochila bostonensis (holotype collection FH: BHI-F 0974) a 1 - 3, a 5 fresh apothecia a 4 dried apothecia b 1 excipular tissues in median section b 2 cells at the base b 3 cells at the upper and lower flank c 1, c 2 paraphyses d 1, d 2 asci d 3 ascus pore with inamyloid reaction d 4 crozier at ascus base e 1 - e 6 ascospores. Mounted in: Congo Red (c 2, d 2, d 4, e 3, e 5), H 2 O (b 1 - b 3, c 1, d 1, e 1, e 2), KOH (e 4), MLZ (d 3, e 6). Scale bars: 500 µm (a 1 - a 5); 50 µm (b 1); 10 µm (b 1, b 2, c 1, c 2, d 1 - d 4, e 1 - e 6)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/507852" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

